title: The Problem With Wall Street’s Top Dividend Stocks For 2020
text: As always, we wish Wall Street suits the best for 2020. But they are four years late on this call.

title: Stock Market Outlook: Russell 2000 Spurs Holiday Rally
text: In early November, in an interview with stockcharts.com, David Keller and I talked about the “Economic Modern Family” of stock market ETFs and how they seriously lagged the major indices.

title: A 6% January Decline like 2014?
text: Some on Wall Street on comparing this year’s performance of the S&P 500 to that of 2013. There are a surprising number of technical similarities but does that mean we will see a 6% correction in January like we did in 2014?

title: Investing Insights: Contenders to Amazon, SECURE Act, and Enbridge
text: In this week’s podcast, equity analyst Joe Gemino highlights Enbridge as a dividend opportunity, Christine Benz invites Vanguard's Maria Bruno to talk about strategies for young investors, equity analyst Zain Akbari analyzes which brick-and-mortars can contend with Amazon, Daniel Sotiroff shares insights on the evolution of foreign stock index funds, and Christine Benz discusses what SECURE Act means for retirement.

title: Wall Street Week Ahead: History suggests rally may slow for U.S. stocks in 2020
text: The outsized rally in the U.S. stock market this year may give way to a more muted performance in 2020 if history is any guide.
